In this Workshop...

Welcome to an exciting journey into the world of robotics! This workshop is designed for young minds aged 10-15, eager to explore the basics of robotics through interactive, hands-on sessions. Guided by IITians, participants can build their own robots, learn about the fundamentals of robotics, and experience the thrill of bringing their creations to life.

​

What to Expect:

  • Introduction to Robotics: Discover the basic concepts of robotics, including sensors, actuators, and controllers.

  • Hands-On Activities: Engage in fun, practical sessions where you’ll design, build, and program your own robot.

  • Team Collaboration: Work in groups to solve challenges, encouraging teamwork and creative problem-solving.

  • Showcase & Feedback: Present your robotic creations and receive feedback from mentors and peers.
